headline: Eli Lilly (LLY) Q2 2025 Earnings Call Transcript
summary: Q2 was a strong quarter.  Today we shared positive top line data from the ATTAIN-1 orforglipron trial in people with obesity.  In ATTAIN-1, patients taking the highest dose of orforglipron lost more than 27 pounds or 12.4% of their body weight.

headline: ABBV vs. MRK: An Oncology-Immunology Showdown for Investors
summary: ABBV has rebounded after Humira patent cliff, with Skyrizi and Rinvoq driving growth. Rising estimates and a pipeline set to power earnings into 2029 bode well.

headline: January 2026's Stocks That May Be Trading Below Estimated Value
summary: Amid recent market volatility, the U.S. stock indices have shown resilience with a sharp rebound following geopolitical tensions and tariff threats. As investors navigate these fluctuations, identifying stocks that may be trading below their estimated value can present opportunities for those looking to capitalize on potential market inefficiencies.

headline: Top Picks 2026- Eli Lilly  Co. LLY
summary: Eli Lilly & Co. (LLY) needs little introduction, as it’s probably the most popular drug stock in the world right now thanks to Mounjaro (diabetes) and Zepbound (weight loss), which are the same drug selling well under both indications. But we still think the stock can surprise on the upside going forward, says Mike Cintolo, chief investment strategist at Cabot Wealth Network.
